  "instructions": [
    "Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "Drain and rinse the garbanzo beans.",
    "In a large skillet or saucepan, heat olive oil over medium heat. Add onion and garlic; cook until soft, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add olives, sun-dried tomatoes, red pepper flakes, basil leaves, thyme sprigs, cherry tomatoes, and zucchini. Stir well to combine all ingredients.",
    "Fold in the garbanzo beans and reduce heat to low. Simmer for 10 minutes or until most of liquid has evaporated.",
    "Transfer mixture to a baking dish. Bake for 25-30 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time.",
    "Serve warm as a main course."
